Ecological notes : common in broad-leaved woodland; ancient woodland with oak, hazel and bramble; conifer plantations; heathland (heather) with oak and holly; grounds of horticultural research station; gardens; island with seabird colonies. Reared from the fungi
Hypholoma fasciculare
,
Sparassis crispa
; soil taken from rabbit burrow; nests of blackbird, sand martin, song thrush, house sparrow, linnet, rook, moorhen, magpie, little owl, grey squirrel, brown rat and hedgehog; wasp nest; tit nestbox; decoy nest; from mushrooms and poinsettia compost. i–xii.
